Author:
Vol / Page:  4
Edition:
Quote:  Another interesting specimen of Maori art is an elaborately-carved feeding tube.   This article was once used to convey liquid nourishment to persons undergoing the tattooing process, who were therefore in a very tapu condition, and debarred from handling food.
